notes:
We gratefully accept your clean, dry, re-usable donations of household items, hardware and rebuilding materials. Look for the donations here sign and bring your items to the attendant at the donations building.  Visit website for details.

We do not accept:

 Styrofoam (except polystyrene packing peanuts for reuse)
 Fireworks, ammunition, firearms, explosives of any kind
 Asbestos in any form
 Putrid trash, sewage and septic pumpings or animal carcasses larger than 60 pounds
 Liquids (except used veggie oil & used motor oil)
 Medical or bio-waste including sharps.

Please do not leave a gift of recycling or trash at the gate during closed hours. Not only does this attract critters, but you could be fined up to $1,000 for illegal litteringwho wants that to happen?
